<img class="img-fluid" src="../img/meal-app/meal-header.png">

Meal planning is often the most tedious part of fitness. Counting macros, balancing calories, and figuring out what to cook can take more energy than the workout itself. My AI-Powered Meal Planner aims to remove this friction. The app accepts an inventory of foods the user already has and their macro goals, then outputs a daily meal plan that balances both.  

I focused on backend development, where I designed logic to calculate macros dynamically and generate balanced meals. Instead of building a chatbot, I wanted a silent assistant that produced results in a straightforward way. On the technical side, I integrated AI libraries for optimization, but prioritized efficiency and clarity in the final output.  

This project taught me how to merge data science principles with user experience design. I learned how to balance flexibility with accuracyâ€”users may have inconsistent pantry data, so the system must adapt while still producing valid plans. The process also deepened my understanding of applied AI outside of chat-based contexts, showing how automation can serve everyday needs.  

